# Changelog / version entries (Forsa)

When a task ships **user-visible** behavior (dashboard, portal, mobile-facing flows), update the changelog in the same change unless it is purely internal.

## Where

- Data: [`src/features/changelog/data/releases.yaml`](src/features/changelog/data/releases.yaml)
- Types: [`src/features/changelog/types/index.ts`](src/features/changelog/types/index.ts) (only if the schema changes)
- UI labels only (headers, `changelog.type.*`): [`src/translations/en.ts`](src/translations/en.ts), [`src/translations/ar.ts`](src/translations/ar.ts). Release copy stays in YAML (`en` / `ar` per field).

## When it is **required**

Add or extend a release entry for:

- New **features** or user-facing capability
- **Bug fixes** that users could notice or that fixed broken flows
- Meaningful **improvements** (performance, reliability, UX that changes how people work)
- **Breaking** or workflow changes users must know (`type: changed`)

Use `type`: `added` | `fixed` | `improved` | `changed`. Set `sidebarPath` when the change maps to a sidebar route (drives the **NEW** badge logic).

## When **not** to mention

Skip changelog lines for:

- Typo-only, comment-only, or purely internal refactors
- Trivial layout tweaks with no meaningful user outcome
- Dependency bumps with no visible behavior change

If unsure: **one short line** is better than silence for anything a support or ops person would care about.

## Format (YAML)

- New **semver** block at the **top** of the array (newest first).
- Each `title` and each entry `description` must include **`en`** and **`ar`**.
- Keep bullets factual; avoid marketing fluff.

## Example entry shape

```yaml
- version: "1.4.0"
  date: "2026-05-14"
  title:
    en: "Short English title"
    ar: "عنوان عربي قصير"
  entries:
    - description:
        en: "Fixed X when doing Y."
        ar: "تم إصلاح X عند القيام بـ Y."
      type: fixed
      sidebarPath: /auctions
```
